<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tokumaru]]></name></author>
<updated>2014-01-02T11:24:25-07:00</updated>
<published>2014-01-02T11:24:25-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10839&amp;p=123158#p123158</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10839&amp;p=123158#p123158"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: About glitches]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10839&amp;p=123158#p123158"><![CDATA[
Some games (mostly early ones) set the vertical scroll to -1 in order to compensate for the 1 scanline delay in sprite coordinates. This may cause attribute table data to be rendered as name table data in the first scanline of the screen, which most of the time will look like garbage. Since this isn't visible in most TVs, the problem was never detected by the developers. You should check each game (in other emulators and possibly a real console though video capture) to verify whether it's supposed to have those glitches before trying to fix them.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Jan 02, 2014 11:24 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
